sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Task (PL0)
    participant HW as CPU Hardware
    participant Vec as Exception Vectors
    participant Kernel as Kernel Handler (PL1)
    participant Sched as Scheduler

    Note over User, HW: CPSR.M = USR (0x10)

    %% Scenario 1: Syscall Yield
    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
    Note over User, Sched: Scenario 1: Software Interrupt (SVC)
    User->>HW: SVC #0 (Yield)
    activate HW
    Note right of HW: SPSR_svc = CPSR<br/>LR_svc = PC (Next Instr)<br/>CPSR.M = SVC
    HW->>Vec: Jump to 0x08
    deactivate HW
    
    Vec->>Kernel: b svc_handler
    activate Kernel
    Kernel->>Kernel: PUSH {R0-R12, LR} (Save Context)
    Kernel->>Sched: scheduler_yield()
    
    Note right of Sched: Swap SP (Current -> Next)
    
    Sched-->>Kernel: New Task Context Ready
    Kernel->>Kernel: POP {R0-R12, LR} (Load Context)
    Kernel->>HW: MOVS PC, LR (Exception Return)
    deactivate Kernel
    
    HW-->>User: Resume User Task
    end

    %% Scenario 2: IRQ Preemption
    rect rgb(255, 240, 240)
    Note over User, Sched: Scenario 2: Hardware Interrupt (IRQ)
    User->>HW: External IRQ Triggered
    activate HW
    Note right of HW: SPSR_irq = CPSR<br/>LR_irq = PC + 4<br/>CPSR.M = IRQ
    HW->>Vec: Jump to 0x18
    deactivate HW
    
    Vec->>Kernel: b irq_handler
    activate Kernel
    Note right of Kernel: Handle Hardware (Clear Flags)
    Kernel-->>Sched: Time Slice Expired?
    
    Kernel->>HW: LDM ... PC^ (Exception Return)
    deactivate Kernel
    
    activate HW
    Note right of HW: CPSR = SPSR_irq<br/>PC = LR_irq - 4
    HW-->>User: Resume User Task
    deactivate HW
    end